<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-08T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-08T07:00:00-05:00" n="1038" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1038">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123G98/28</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Wheeler</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-08T21:00:00+09:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It is my painful duty to inform you that the Ambassador died suddenly at
                            8 tonight of apoplexy. In accordance with instructions to diplomatic
                            officers, I have assumed charge as Chargé d’Affaires <hi rend="italic">ad interim.</hi>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>